field.groups0.parameters0.name: min_ang
field.groups0.parameters0.description: The angle of the first range measurement. The unit depends on ~ang_radians.
field.groups0.parameters1.name: max_ang
field.groups0.parameters1.description: The angle of the first range measurement. The unit depends on ~ang_radians.
field.groups0.parameters2.name: intensity
field.groups0.parameters2.description: Whether or not the hokuyo returns intensity values.
field.groups0.parameters3.name: cluster
field.groups0.parameters3.description: The number of adjacent range measurements to cluster into a single reading
field.groups0.parameters4.name: skip
field.groups0.parameters4.description: The number of scans to skip between each measured scan
field.groups0.parameters5.name: port
field.groups0.parameters5.description: The serial port where the hokuyo device can be found
field.groups0.parameters6.name: calibrate_time
field.groups0.parameters6.description: Whether the node should calibrate the hokuyo's time offset
field.groups0.parameters7.name: frame_id
field.groups0.parameters7.description: The frame in which laser scans will be returned
field.groups0.parameters8.name: time_offset
field.groups0.parameters8.description: An offet to add to the timestamp before publication of a scan
field.groups0.parameters9.name: allow_unsafe_settings
field.groups0.parameters9.description: Turn this on if you wish to use the UTM-30LX with an unsafe angular range. Turning this option on may cause occasional crashes or bad data. This option is a tempory workaround that will hopefully be removed in an upcoming driver version.
